> I would say we add `HttpProxy` option to the quadlet file but not other ways to add proxies.

Agree. Quadlet facilitates key to command line argument translation. Therefore, adding keys for argument should always be encouraged. However, the Quadlet sections do not come to replace what should be configured in other systemd sections (same as setting service dependencies).

@ogajduse Care to open a PR for the `HttpProxy` key?
